</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,618,644]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Discussion.</emphasis>
All but the two of the 16 original 
<typeStatus box="[723,830,619,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">paratypes</typeStatus>
were destroyed in the MNRJ fire in 2018. I note that 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M." box="[151,334,655,681]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref41922" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1987) Mirideos neotropicais, CCLXXVIII: Descricoes de duas especies novas de Cyrtocapsus Reuter (Hemiptera). Boletim do Museum Paraense Emilio Goeldi, 3, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1987">Carvalho (1987)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that males were unknown in the original description, even though he listed 
<specimenCount box="[1280,1390,655,681]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="female">14 female</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[151,254,691,717]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="male">two male</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[262,373,691,717]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
